itemDescription: American academic; emigrant to the UK

wikipedia_page.main: Jennifer Chase Barnes (born 30 July 1960) is a musicologist and former university administrator. She was a Pro-Vice-Chancellor and Deputy Vice-Chancellor in the University of Cambridge, and the 4th President of Murray Edwards College, Cambridge’ in the United Kingdom.

response: *1960 – Jennifer Barnes, American-English musicologist and academic

In 1975, the College's President Dame Rosemary Murray became the first woman to hold the post of Vice-Chancellor of the University of Cambridge. Since then, two subsequent presidents, Anne Lonsdale and Jennifer Barnes, have become Pro-Vice-Chancellors of the University of Cambridge.
* Dr Jennifer Barnes (WGH 82–83), President of Murray Edwards College, Cambridge
